textBox.richText: Max had a bday party on sunday, so he and mom headed back saturday night. Originally, the forcasts had called for 3ish inches, but as of saturday, it wasn’t looking good. Enter sunday morning: 7” at WP!!! Woo hoo! Day started off pretty typical...no pano or eagle because of winds. Did Jane laps through the Columbine tress, Harolds+Weather Station, and Tophers until Eagle opened up. Left hand was glorious...fresh tracks pretty much on demand. Kept peeking over until they opened up pano...then it was time for Belle.
